# GitHub reads: prefer REST over GraphQL (global)

Operating principle: **serve GitHub read/metadata needs from REST endpoints,
not GraphQL.** GraphQL shares a separate, easy-to-exhaust rate-limit bucket;
REST is the default transport unless no REST equivalent exists.

**Default transport.**
- Use `gh api <REST path>` — absolute REST path, e.g.
  `gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/pulls/123` or
  `gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/42` — not `gh api graphql`.
- Prefer documented REST resources from
  [GitHub REST API](https://docs.github.com/en/rest) over hand-written GraphQL
  queries.
- When a high-level `gh` subcommand exists and project tooling routes it to
  REST, use that canonical form instead of inventing a one-off query.

**Forbidden when REST can serve the datum.**
- `gh api graphql` and inline GraphQL query strings.
- Raw `curl` (or similar) to `api.github.com` for reads that have a documented
  REST equivalent.
- Throwaway temporary `gh` shims whose only purpose is to bypass a REST-first
  path.

**When GraphQL quota is exhausted.** Do not improvise GraphQL, curl, or shims.
Switch to the REST endpoint for the same datum (or the project's REST-routed
`gh` form). If the needed argv shape is uncovered, **report** it for inventory
extension — do not paper over the gap with GraphQL.

**When REST has no equivalent.** Rare APIs exposed only via GraphQL, or writes
that `gh` documents as GraphQL-backed — use native `gh` and note the gap. Still
do not hand-roll raw `curl` when `gh api` can carry the call.

**orchestrator-pack override.** In this repository, the stricter **`gh` wrapper
transport** section in `prompts/agent_rules.md` supersedes this hint: every
GitHub read goes through pack `scripts/gh` on PATH and inventory-listed
canonical forms. Follow that section when working here.

This is a prompt-level obligation (you see the rule and follow it), not a hard
hook.
